      "content": "gotcha. so it's more about the actual hardware/tech costs than just bureaucracy. do you think the long-term \"innovation\" or \"sustainability\" benefits you mentioned actually offset these kinds of costs for a small business, or are those just theoretical advantages that don't really help a shop trying to survive right now?",
